name: Project Mercury Sketch
description:
Project Mercury was the first human spaceflight program of the United States, running from 1958 through 1963. An early highlight of the Space Race, its goal was to put a man into Earth orbit and return him safely, ideally before the Soviet Union. Wikipedia
Started: 1958
Completed: 1963
First flight: August 21, 1959
Last flight: May 15, 1963
Start date: 1958
